# EL-materialization: the inverse of futuram:hasDirectPart.
#
# futuram:hasDirectPart owl:inverseOf futuram:isDirectPartOf is an OWL axiom OUTSIDE
# the EL profile — ELK (and the reasoner-free TDB2 serving layer) will NOT
# materialise the inverse. The component-layer definitions quantify over
# isDirectPartOf, so without this edge the top-down layer inference cannot fire.
#
# This CONSTRUCT asserts the inverse explicitly, so the conclusion is present as
# data and no inverse-property reasoning is needed at query time. The owl:inverseOf
# axiom stays in the TBox as the SPECIFICATION (HermiT / the test suite validate
# it); this rule precomputes its one consequence.
PREFIX futuram: <https://www.purl.org/futuram#>

CONSTRUCT { ?part futuram:isDirectPartOf ?whole . }
WHERE     { ?whole futuram:hasDirectPart ?part . }
